10.18.23  7:59 pm   When you sing "it's the Cambrian explosionnn" in history of the world, you seem to be using an Ab maj pentatonic scale and then play a Bbmin7 (add4) for "splowww" and a Bmaj (add2) for "shunnn".

Where do you get this B from?

     the standard equal tempered tuning system

     Is this just about the mostly chromatic movement or is there some functional harmony thing I'm missing?

     if you liked it, then you didn't miss it. on the other hand, if you found it distracting, awkward, or bad, or if you felt it brought the video down at that moment and made it worse, then that means either you or i indeed missed something

     How does Bill think of it?

     it's just like the way we think of the words we use to describe things. i actually don't know how we do that

     Also, I like the things I know you've done so thanks for doing them and sharing them.
